% C++ Language Ontology - CNL Format
% Extends oo_ontology.cnl with C++-specific concepts
%
% This ontology maps C++-specific concepts to the generic OO ontology.
% All C++ entities should use the unified CNL names with language="cpp".

% ============================================================================
% C++-Specific Entity Types
% ============================================================================

% File types
Every cpp-translation-unit is a translation-unit.
Every cpp-header-file is a translation-unit.
Every cpp-source-file is a translation-unit.

% Namespace
Every cpp-namespace is a namespace.
Every anonymous-namespace is a cpp-namespace.

% Type definitions
Every cpp-class is a class.
Every cpp-struct is a struct.
Every cpp-union is a union.
Every cpp-enum is an enum.
Every cpp-enum-class is a cpp-enum.
Every cpp-template is a template.
Every cpp-type-def is a type-def.
Every cpp-using-alias is a type-alias.

% Members
Every cpp-method is a method.
Every cpp-function is a function.
Every cpp-constructor is a constructor.
Every cpp-destructor is a destructor.
Every cpp-field is a field.
Every cpp-static-field is a cpp-field.

% Parameters
Every cpp-parameter is a parameter.
Every cpp-const-parameter is a cpp-parameter.
Every cpp-reference-parameter is a cpp-parameter.
Every cpp-pointer-parameter is a cpp-parameter.

% Preprocessor
Every cpp-include is an include.
Every cpp-macro is a macro.
Every cpp-define is a cpp-macro.

% Variables
Every cpp-variable is a variable.
Every cpp-global-variable is a cpp-variable.
Every cpp-local-variable is a cpp-variable.

% References
Every cpp-reference is a reference.

% ============================================================================
% C++-Specific Concepts
% ============================================================================

% Templates
Every class-template is a template.
Every function-template is a template.
Every template-specialization is a template.
Every template-instantiation is a template.

% Virtual functions
Every virtual-method is a method.
Every pure-virtual-method is a virtual-method.
Every override-method is a method.

% Special member functions
Every copy-constructor is a constructor.
Every move-constructor is a constructor.
Every copy-assignment is a method.
Every move-assignment is a method.

% Operators
Every operator-overload is a function.
Every conversion-operator is a operator-overload.

% Friends
Every friend-function is a function.
Every friend-class is a class.

% Inheritance
Every virtual-base is a class.
Every multiple-inheritance-class is a class.

% ============================================================================
% C++ Access Specifiers (as concepts)
% ============================================================================

Every public-member is a member.
Every private-member is a member.
Every protected-member is a member.

% ============================================================================
% C++ Memory Management
% ============================================================================

% RAII pattern
Every raii-class is a class.
Every resource-acquiring-constructor is a constructor.
Every resource-releasing-destructor is a destructor.

% Smart pointers
Every unique-ptr-field is a field.
Every shared-ptr-field is a field.
Every weak-ptr-field is a field.

% ============================================================================
% C++ Code Smells
% ============================================================================

% Rule of Three/Five violations
Every rule-of-three-violation is a class.
Every rule-of-five-violation is a class.

% Missing virtual destructor
Every missing-virtual-destructor is a class.

% Slicing risk
Every slicing-risk-class is a class.

% God class
Every cpp-god-class is a god-class.

% Large function
Every cpp-long-function is a long-method.
